About the job

Are you passionate about data exploration and creating innovative visualisations, with a strong ambition to thrive in the finance industry?


Our Hedge Fund client is seeking experienced Frontend and Full-Stack Developers to join their elite team of UI engineers. These teams are focused on building high-performance user interfaces and scalable, maintainable cross-platform applications.


Using cutting-edge frontend technologies such as JavaScript, TypeScript, React, HTML5, and CSS, alongside advanced data visualisation tools like D3, ChartIQ, and eCharts, you’ll push boundaries to develop the next generation of investment platforms.


While prior financial knowledge isn’t a requirement, a genuine interest in the sector will give you an edge.


This role offers a unique opportunity to collaborate with traders, analysts, and quantitative researchers, designing in-house applications that have a real impact on end users. With world-class training and extensive exposure, this position provides the perfect platform to accelerate your career in a dynamic, high-growth environment.

About the company

NJF Global Holdings Ltd
32,306 followers
Staffing and Recruiting 51-200 employees 35 on LinkedIn

NJF is a tech-focused company whose by-product is recruitment. Our reputation among many of the world’s leading institutions has resulted in a prolific demand for our services and the continued expansion of our international network.

NJF’s focus is within the Trading and Technology markets. Our interrelated teams employ rigorous research methodologies to ensure that we are at the forefront of the latest trends in both spheres. Our consultants are devoted to unearthing world-class talent and guiding the right people into the right jobs.

At NJF, we make the individual our priority. This, in turn, strengthens our comprehensive knowledge of the market and drives our continuous research effort.
Along with taking the time to gain a deep understanding of each candidate’s technical skills and market experience, we also get to know them as people. This ensures that our efforts result in a long-term, lasting relationship for both client and candidate.

Our Trading Practice coordinates the careers of high-performing traders, quants and data scientists across the upper echelons of quantitative managers: hedge funds, proprietary trading organizations and tech firms.

Our Technology Practice has a track record of finding the very best developers and infrastructure experts to build world-class systems and frameworks for high frequency proprietary trading firms, hedge funds and technology start-ups. We recognize that organizations want their staff to reflect the world’s diverse population. We are committed to identifying, attracting and cultivating promising talent from the broadest possible spectrum of professionals. Our continued success has enabled us to build long-standing relationships and to expand our list of contacts in a wide range of communities; this further enhances our ability to deliver.
